"title": "2555: Jesus Christ, resurrection appearances of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2555",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ appeared to various groups and individuals on several occasions after his death, prior to his ascension into heaven.</p>\n<h2>The resurrection appearances of Jesus Christ on the third day</h2>\n<h3>To Mary Magdalene</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:10-John20:18\">JHN 20:10–20:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:9-Mark16:11\">MRK 16:9–16:11</a></p>\n<h3>To the women at the tomb</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:1-Matt28:10\">MAT 28:1–28:10</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:1-Mark16:8\">MRK 16:1–16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:1-Luke24:12\">LUK 24:1–24:12</a></p>\n<h3>To Peter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:34\">LUK 24:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:5\">1CO 15:5</a></p>\n<h3>To the two travellers to Emmaus</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:12-Mark16:13\">MRK 16:12–16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:13-Luke24:16\">LUK 24:13–24:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:30-Luke24:32\">LUK 24:30–24:32</a></p>\n<h3>To the disciples in the upper room</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:14\">MRK 16:14</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:36\">LUK 24:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:19\">JHN 20:19</a></p>\n<h2>Further appearances of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>To the disciples in the upper room</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:26\">JHN 20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:5\">1CO 15:5</a></p>\n<h3>Other appearances</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:1\">JHN 21:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:16-Matt28:17\">MAT 28:16–28:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:6-1Cor15:7\">1CO 15:6–15:7</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ appears at his ascension</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:19\">MRK 16:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:50-Luke24:51\">LUK 24:50–24:51</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:9\">ACT 1:9</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's resurrection body</h2>\n<h3>It was different from his pre-crucifixion body</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:26\">JHN 20:26</a></strong> <em>This suggests that the resurrected body of Jesus Christ was not restricted by natural laws: closed doors provided no barrier to Jesus Christ's bodily appearance to his disciples.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:12\">MRK 16:12</a> <em>The failure to recognise Jesus Christ may be an indication of his changed appearance but also might emphasise the disciples' own sorrow and lack of faith</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:14\">JHN 20:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:19\">JHN 20:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:36\">LUK 24:36</a></p>\n<h3>It was a body of flesh and blood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:39\">LUK 24:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:42-Luke24:43\">LUK 24:42–24:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:20\">JHN 20:20</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ foretold his resurrection appearances</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:16\">JHN 16:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Responses to Jesus Christ's resurrection appearances</h2>\n<h3>Fear and alarm</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:37\">LUK 24:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:10\">MAT 28:10</a></p>\n<h3>Doubt and disbelief</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:11\">MRK 16:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:17\">MAT 28:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:13-Mark16:14\">MRK 16:13–16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:11-Luke24:12\">LUK 24:11–24:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:9\">JHN 20:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:13-John20:14\">JHN 20:13–20:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:25\">JHN 20:25</a></p>\n<h3>Belief and joy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:8\">MAT 28:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:31-Luke24:32\">LUK 24:31–24:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:41\">LUK 24:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:16\">JHN 20:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:18\">JHN 20:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:27-John20:29\">JHN 20:27–20:29</a></p>\n<h3>Understanding and worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:9\">MAT 28:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:8\">LUK 24:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:45-Luke24:47\">LUK 24:45–24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:22\">JHN 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:31-Acts2:33\">ACT 2:31–2:33</a></p>\n<h2>The significance of Jesus Christ's resurrection appearances</h2>\n<h3>They gave proof of Jesus Christ's deity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:28-John20:29\">JHN 20:28–20:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:31-Luke24:34\">LUK 24:31–24:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:8\">JHN 20:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:41-Acts10:42\">ACT 10:41–10:42</a></p>\n<h3>Christian life and faith depend on the trustworthiness of the witnesses' testimony</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:17\">1CO 15:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:31\">JHN 20:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:15\">ACT 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:1-1Cor15:58\">1CO 15:1–15:58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:14\">1TH 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:3\">1PE 1:3</a></p>",
